place.name: BAGTHORPE
place.gazetteerText: BAGTHORPE, a parish in Docking district, Norfolk; 7½ miles N by W of Rougham, and 9 WNW of Fakenham r. station. Post Town, Bircham under Rougham. Acres, 750. Real property, £830. Pop., 69. Houses, 14. The property is divided among a few. Bagthorpe Hall is a chief residence. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £125. Patron, the Rev. S. R. Cattley. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
